            "id": "566d8fb511c94a27a9943",
            "questionText": "A large data center is auditing its power consumption. One server rack consumed $!$18 \\text{ MWh}$!$ of electrical energy in one month. Given that $!$1 \\text{ MWh} = 3.6 \\times 10^9 \\text{ J}$!$ and a month has $!$30$!$ days, calculate the average electrical power (in Watts) that this server rack drew during that month.",
            "imageText": "",
            "steps": [
                {
                    "id": "7cafc981562f4d43a900e",
                    "stepText": "Let's start by recalling the concept of electrical power. Identify the correct formula to compute power as the rate at which energy is transferred.",
