            "id": "1dc3ffd7949949eb95e8a",
            "questionText": "During routine maintenance, a factory technician measures the electric potentials in an industrial machine and finds that at point A the potential is $!$240\\,\\text{V}$!$ and at point B it is $!$225\\,\\text{V}$!$. If the faulty component between these points dissipates $!$450\\,\\text{J}$!$ of electrical potential energy during operation, calculate the total charge (in Coulombs) that has passed through the component using the formula $!$V = \\frac{\\Delta E}{Q}$!$.",
            "imageText": "",
            "steps": [
                {
                    "id": "17e03f7e0c784f43893e5",
                    "stepText": "Let's start by determining the voltage drop across the component by finding the difference between the potentials at point A and point B. What is the potential difference $!$\\Delta V$!$?",
                    "stepText2": "",
                    "stepImage": "",
                    "stepSolveAnswer": [
                        "15"
                    ],
                    "stepSolveAnswerUnits": "V",
                    "stepConcepts": [
